NAME
     entr - Run arbitrary commands when files change

SYNOPSIS
     entr [script] [args {} ...]

DESCRIPTION
     The entr utility reads a list of files provided on STDIN and run the
     supplied command if any of them change.

EXAMPLES
     To watch for changes in any Python file and run some tests:

           $ find. -name *.py | entr ./test.sh

